{"detail":"---\n\n## DECOMPOSE Report — Issue #24\n\n### What's being asked\nRemove the dead `lint-clean` rule (the SwiftLint rule) from the `swiftStandardPolicy` constant in `cmd\/certify\/init_cmd.go`. This rule references a `lint_errors` metric that no collector supplies, causing fabricated grades for Swift repos. The fix is a straight deletion — no new collector, no other template changes.\n\n---\n\n### Concrete facts found\n\n#### 1. The target block — lines 709–716 of `cmd\/certify\/init_cmd.go`\n\n```\n709:   - id: lint-clean\n710:     dimension: correctness\n711:     description: \"SwiftLint must report zero errors\"\n712:     severity: error\n713:     metric: lint_errors\n714:     threshold: 0\n715:\n716: (blank)\n```\n\nThat's **7 YAML lines + 1 blank line = 8 lines** to remove. Line 711 is the **only occurrence of the string \"SwiftLint\" in any `.go` file** in the repo.\n\n#### 2. After removal, `swiftStandardPolicy` will have 3 rules\n- `test-pass` (lines 717–722)\n- `no-todos` (lines 724–729)\n- `max-complexity` (lines 731–735)\n\n#### 3. How `swiftStandardPolicy` is wired\n- Defined at line 704 as a raw string constant\n- Returned by `languagePolicy(\"swift\")` at line 307 in the same file\n- `languagePolicy` is called by `initCmd.RunE` to generate the `.certification\/policies\/swift-standard.yml` file when a user runs `certify init` in a Swift repo\n\n#### 4. Test impact — **zero breakage expected**\n| Test | Relevant check | Why it survives |\n|------|---------------|-----------------|\n| `cmd\/certify\/cli_test.go:93` — `TestLanguagePolicy_AllSupported` | `languagePolicy(\"swift\") != \"\"` | Only checks non-empty, not content |\n| `internal\/policy\/evaluator_test.go` | Uses `lint-clean` as a mock rule ID | Not Swift-specific; constructs generic Go mock rules |\n| `internal\/engine\/scorer_test.go:150` | Uses `lint-clean` in a scoring table | Generic fixture, not tied to swiftStandardPolicy |\n| `internal\/engine\/pipeline_test.go:15,51` | Uses `lint-clean` in pipeline mocks | Same — generic rule fixtures |\n| `internal\/engine\/certifier_test.go:27` | Uses `lint-clean` in certifier test | Same — generic |\n| `internal\/integration_test.go:165` | Uses `lint-clean` in E2E test | Same — generic |\n| `internal\/config\/policy_test.go:99` | Expects `swift-standard` pack name | Loads from `testdata\/policies\/swift-standard.yml` (a **separate file**), NOT the constant |\n\n#### 5. The `testdata\/policies\/swift-standard.yml` file — **out of scope**\nThis file (at `testdata\/policies\/swift-standard.yml`) also contains the `lint-clean` rule, but the issue explicitly limits target files to `cmd\/certify\/init_cmd.go`. The test that references it (`policy_test.go`) only checks that the pack **exists by name** — it doesn't validate rule count or content for swift-standard. So it won't break, but it's a known inconsistency to flag.\n\n#### 6. Project stack\n- **Go 1.25.5**, module `github.com\/iksnae\/code-certification`\n- CLI framework: `github.com\/spf13\/cobra`\n- Build: `go build -o build\/bin\/certify .\/cmd\/certify\/`\n- Test: `go test .\/... -count=1`\n\n#### 7. No `language_tiers.go` exists yet\nThe issue's plan comment suggests referencing `language_tiers.go` in a comment if wrapping rather than removing, but that file doesn't exist (it's from a sibling issue, #25). The recommended approach per the approved plan is **straight removal**, no wrapping comment needed.\n\n---\n\n### Summary for the next phase\n- **File to edit**: `cmd\/certify\/init_cmd.go`\n- **Lines to delete**: 709–716 (8 lines — the `lint-clean` rule block + its trailing blank)\n- **Verification**: `go build .\/cmd\/certify\/` then `go test .\/... -count=1`\n- **Risk**: Low — no tests depend on the content of `swiftStandardPolicy`","at":805830339.195026,"id":"24-1322","outcome":{"note":{}},"ticketId":"24","phase":"decompose"}
